    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @virtuman there's nothing to do that today inside instantsearch.js.\r\n\r\nDoing faceting with Algolia you cannot enrich facet values by default.\r\n\r\nIf what you care about is new items, then you could add a \"new_arrival:true\" field to your hits inside Algolia then use this field in the custom ranking. Doing so will give a ranking boost to new arrivals. Combine this with sorting facet values by \"count\" then you should get a OK experience I guess.\r\n\r\nLet us know",
